node.text:
from @sne_dc - The process of creating a cocktail begins with the glassware. The glass shapes the cocktail and is the first thing we notice when a cocktail is presented. Since I got into mixology, I have always tried to look for sleek and beautifully crafted glassware for my drinks and to no surprise, some of my most used glasses are from @arccardinal. They have the most exquisite styles in their repertoire and their latest Villeneuve collection is no different. Designed in collaboration with Chef @danielboulud , each wine glass is meticulously sculpted using Krysta glass which offers unmatched strength and transparency. Talk about the perfect "clink"! Featured below is their sweet wine glass, a stunner with 9oz capacity, gorgeous shape and a significant base which makes it even more striking. And, it also doubles as a coupette for a libatious cocktail serve. Taking inspiration from this beauty, I have created a light, bubbly refresher which looks even more superb in this lovely stemmed glass.

. Parisian Spritz .
.
30ml Japanese Gin
20ml St. Germain
15ml Yuzu Sake
10ml Campari
Prosecco
.
Stir or throw the ingredients together with ice, and pour in the @arccardinal Sweet Wine Glass over diamond ice. Top with Prosecco.
